e diffuse and varied. Paradoxically, it is the malleability of honour that made it such an enduring social value with very real meaning for early modern men and women.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 19. Feb 2019) 0aHonorxSocial aspectszGreat BritainxHistoryy16th century. 0aHonorxSocial aspectszGreat BritainxHistoryy17th century. 0aSocial psychologyzGreat BritainxHistoryy16th century. 0aSocial psychologyzGreat BritainxHistoryy17th century.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press ebook package 2017z978311063896740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781487512736423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487512736.jpg  a978-3-11-063896-7  University of Toronto Press ebook package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG